# API field errors → forms (frontend)

The backend may return field errors at **`response.data.errors`** (flat) or under **`response.data.details.errors`** (e.g. Nest `BadRequestException`). Do not branch on `error?.response?.data?.errors` alone.

## Required pattern

1. Import from `@/lib/api/types` once that module exists:

   `import { type BaseResponse, getFieldErrorsFromApiResponse } from '@/lib/api/types';`

2. In `catch`, normalize once and map to the form:

```typescript
import { logError } from '@/app/utils/logger';

try {
  await submitForm(values);
} catch (err) {
  const error = err as import('axios').AxiosError<BaseResponse>;
  const fieldErrors = getFieldErrorsFromApiResponse(error?.response?.data);
  if (fieldErrors && Object.keys(fieldErrors).length > 0) {
    Object.entries(fieldErrors).forEach(([key, value]) => {
      if (key in form.getValues()) {
        form.setError(key as keyof YourSchema, { message: value });
      }
    });
  } else {
    logError(error.response?.data?.message ?? 'Request failed', error);
    // Also surface to the user via your toast helper when available.
  }
}
```

Extend **`getFieldErrorsFromApiResponse`** in `lib/api/types.ts` when new error shapes appear—do not duplicate parsing in components.

## Anti-pattern

```typescript
// ❌ Misses nested `details.errors`
if (error?.response?.data?.errors) {
  Object.entries(error.response.data.errors) ...
}
```
